The paper discusses a grid framework for medical image processing that utilizes Hadoop and HBase for data colocation and NoSQL query. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) or Databases (cs.DB) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with image processing, which could place it in the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of MapReduce and load balancing also suggests a possible connection to Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) or Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-categories.
